value.value: 前額の色素沈着減少
visually detectable dilution of pigment present in the forehead
涙骨の矮小化
reduced size of the thin plate that forms part of the medial wall of the orbit behind the frontal process of the maxilla
涙骨の形成不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the lacrimal bone, typically resulting in decreased size
涙骨の欠如
absence of the thin plate that forms part of the medial wall of the orbit behind the frontal process of the maxilla
赤色歯
reddish, brown opalescent discoloration of teeth in normal light
篩骨甲介の欠如
absence of the conchae of the ethmoid bone which normally occupy the caudal part of the nasal fossae and form the lateral and superior portions of the turbinate bones in mammals
鼻窩の欠如

absence of one or both of a pair of depressions formed in the developing face that give rise to the rostral portion of the nasal meatus; the nasal pits indent the frontonasal process and divide it into a medial and two lateral nasal processes
耳窩の欠如
absence of the paired depression of thickened otic placode epithelium marking the location of the future otic vesicles
後鼻孔の狭窄
abnormal narrowing or constriction of either of the pair of posterior apertures of the nasal cavity that open into the nasopharynx
顔のサイズ異常
deviation from the average range of face size for an organism
小さい顔
presence of an abnormally small face
顔の形成不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the face, typically resulting in decreased size
短顔
an abnormally decreased height (length) of the face
細い顔
a reduction in the width of the upper and lower face
大きい顔
presence of an abnormally large face
幅広い顔
increased width of the upper and lower face
長い顔
an abnormally increased height (length) of the face
顔の形態異常
any anomaly in the characteristic surface outline or contour of the face
丸い顔
facial appearance is more circular than usual as viewed from the front
四角い顔
facial contours, as viewed from the front, show a broad upper face/cranium and lower face/mandible, creating a square appearance
粗な顔
absence of fine and sharp appearance of facial features, usually because of rounded and heavy features or thickened skin with or without thickening of subcutaneous and bony tissues
有毛性耳介
excessive hair growth on the external ear; may involve the meatal opening, pinnae or external rim
頭蓋腔の形態異常
any anomaly of the space formed within the skull and occupied by the brain, pineal and hypophysis cerebri, parts of the cranial and spinal nerves, blood vessels, meninges and cerebrospinal fluid
頭蓋腔の狭小化
reduced size of the space formed within the skull and occupied by the brain, pineal and hypophysis cerebri, parts of the cranial and spinal nerves, blood vessels, meninges and cerebrospinal fluid
合耳症
fusion or abnormal approximation of the ears in front of the neck, often accompanied by the absence or defective development of the lower jaw
小さい切歯
reduced size of the set of long teeth that are the most anterior and prominent in the jaw
小さい下切歯
reduced size of the lower set of long teeth that are the most anterior and prominent in the jaw
小さい上切歯
reduced size of the upper set of long teeth that are the most anterior and prominent in the jaw
長い下切歯
increased length or overgrowth of the lower set of long teeth that are the most anterior and prominent in the jaw
長い上切歯
increased length or overgrowth of the upper set of long teeth that are the most anterior and prominent in the jaw
鼓膜輪の形成不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the tympanic ring, typically resulting in decreased size
顎癒合症（顎間索）

fusion of the upper and lower jaw; fusion can range from simple mucosal bands (synechiae) to complete bony fusion (synostosis); syngnathia can occur in the midline, or laterally, and it can be uni- or bilateral
多骨性の顎癒合症（顎間索）
bony fusion of the upper and lower jaw
線維性の顎癒合症（顎間索）
complete or nearly complete soft tissue fusion of the alveolar ridges
矮小歯（小歯症）
abnormal reduction in the size of one or more teeth
短い下切歯
reduced length of the lower set of long teeth that are the most anterior and prominent in the jaw
短い上切歯
reduced length of the upper set of long teeth that are the most anterior and prominent in the jaw
巨大歯
abnormal increase in the size of one or more teeth
耳輪の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the outer rim of the ear that extends from the insertion of the ear on the scalp (root) to the termination of the cartilage at the earlobe
上顎洞の欠如

definition.value: absence of the largest of the paranasal sinuses, a paired pyramid-shaped air sinus located within the maxillary bone which drains via the maxillary ostium into the infundibulum, then through the hiatus semilunaris into the middle meatus of the nose

value.value: 大後頭孔狭窄
abnormal narrowing or constriction of the large orifice in the occipital bone through which the spinal cord passes to the cranial cavity and becomes continuous with the medulla oblongata
顔面中部の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the midface region which extends, superiorly, from the inferior orbital margin to, inferiorly, the level of nasal base; it is formed by the maxilla (upper jaw) and zygoma and cheeks and malar region; traditionally, the nose and premaxilla are not included in the midface
耳周囲の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the region around the ear
耳前瘻孔
small indentation anterior to the insertion of the ear
上眼瞼膨満
increase in periorbital soft tissue
顔面非対称
an abnormal difference between the left and right sides of the face
片側顔面形成不全
unilateral decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the facial tissues, including muscles and bones, typically resulting in decreased size of one side of the face
虫歯

formation of cavities in the teeth due to a multifactorial bacterial infection that causes demineralization and destruction of the hard tissues of the teeth (enamel, dentin and cementum), usually by production of acid by bacterial fermentation of the food debris accumulated on the tooth surface
眼窩蝶形骨の欠如
missing the bone that is situated in the orbit on either side of the presphenoid; it generally forms a part of the sphenoid in the adult, and may be independent in the young
眼窩の形態異常
any anomaly in the characteristic surface outline or contour of the orbits of an organism
